<subSubSection id="06082E4E1691989A971CB4A022F76DAB" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="notes">
<paragraph id="CB59A7826D2734A1BAECAE434889F67A" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="442DDD6934B5F652791168E65A77D135" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="7DC86CB220770C4DC4308201B0824C7A" authorityName="Q. R. Li, J. C. Kang &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila clypeata" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis id="F28472D4F15125C230D47C9E6FCFFA71" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has long and weakly striate ascospores similar to 
<taxonomicName id="15A93D15E952C218ED793F32D42986D2" genus="A." lsidName="A. coronata" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="coronata">
<emphasis id="D47AD6F0C527326EF2CF8B5B9B80F619" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. coronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Rehm) Umali &amp; K.D. Hyde, 
<taxonomicName id="B3B0B8226A4588B3B3DA3E3B0247791D" genus="A." lsidName="A. serrulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="serrulata">
<emphasis id="0248FDB879CB95FF066F1033BB44ACFD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. serrulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ellis &amp; G. Martin) K.D. Hyde and 
<taxonomicName id="9D91919E2ADD41B4F9E4ACB2070E973B" genus="A." lsidName="A. bambusae" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="bambusae">
<emphasis id="2777209259D15A9E03E9A509158B0CD8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. bambusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="ECA9E2E6ED7FAEE45FA5E16DB6C07E68" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B19" refString="Hyde, KD, 1996. Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63(1/2): 81-100." title="Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 / 2): 81 - 100." year="1996">Hyde 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="83AF943FD8EE31F75CFDB3350981198A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464296" author="Umali, TE" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="185 - 188" refId="B54" refString="Umali, TE, Hyde, KD, Quimio, TH, 1999. Arecophila bambusae sp. nov. and A. coronata comb. nov., from dead culms of bamboo. Mycoscience 40 (2): 185 - 188, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464296" title="Arecophila bambusae sp. nov. and A. coronata comb. nov., from dead culms of bamboo." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464296" volume="40" year="1999">Umali et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="0025570D42DCD7283890CF10B5EB7580" genus="A." lsidName="A. coronata" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="coronata">
<emphasis id="93FD192BADD5C36ED33F541694DE205E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. coronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not have a prominent clypeus and has longer and fusiform ascospores. 
<taxonomicName id="CB2D0B154B790D3C0952018D76572541" authorityName="Q. R. Li, J. C. Kang &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila clypeata" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis id="B618B4E1B445A906469A9F5B1A2B983D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="6FE27F779D2BC13337BFAB90744F02A3" genus="A." lsidName="A. serrulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="serrulata">
<emphasis id="8000EAF7485795D6D956A9FE8C03A8E9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. serrulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the ascomata without a central papilla surrounded by a circle of white tissue, further in having ascospores with wide sheaths (
<bibRefCitation id="749148900659246BADAD0038C2DFC8F4" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B19" refString="Hyde, KD, 1996. Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63(1/2): 81-100." title="Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 / 2): 81 - 100." year="1996">Hyde 1996</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="86D5DF5391ED61B1A58505EF15033E55" authorityName="Q. R. Li, J. C. Kang &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila clypeata" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis id="35B0A6C173AE2856F2F9F7653F43EF1B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="42D55CCBE3A3CAAC4540CACA46B58856" genus="A." lsidName="A. bambusae" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="bambusae">
<emphasis id="839BE7A57E8D27EC9F6FE5E0B714CC28" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. bambusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which, however, has narrower ascospores (19-22.5 
<normalizedToken id="632CFCF1F53D0159683FD486289170BA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5.5-7 
<normalizedToken id="C904F3556814D492677758A0F9F19E82" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) covered by the strong striations and has ascomata without a central papilla surrounded by a black corolla protuberance (
<bibRefCitation id="3CC74C5CE6774530397CD961D4813FDF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464296" author="Umali, TE" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="185 - 188" refId="B54" refString="Umali, TE, Hyde, KD, Quimio, TH, 1999. Arecophila bambusae sp. nov. and A. coronata comb. nov., from dead culms of bamboo. Mycoscience 40 (2): 185 - 188, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464296" title="Arecophila bambusae sp. nov. and A. coronata comb. nov., from dead culms of bamboo." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464296" volume="40" year="1999">Umali et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
